<svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 23, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cpe1705582470714_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cpe1705582470714_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cpe1705582470714_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fir1665702809557\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Create and Maintain Glyphs \n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Glyphs are maintained and deployed in a runtime library.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"fir1665702809557__context_w3918ab1b5b1_w3919ab1b5_w3920ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"fir1665702809557__topic_d27203e1_d27204e1_d27205e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fir1665702809557__p_d27206e1_d27207e1_d27208e1\">Using your preferred graphical tools, create one or more images to use as sources for the glyph items. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nbf1705582294349.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nbf1705582294349.html\" title=\"Glyphs are images in a Uniface-proprietary format, which can be used as background images in forms, entities and application shells, and as icons in widgets, panel buttons, menus, and drag-and-drop formats.\">Glyphs</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13886e1_d13887e1_d13888e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Open the glyph editor:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13889e1_d13890e1_d13891e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Editors</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Glyphs</span></span>. </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13892e1_d13893e1_d13894e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"fir1665702809557__p_d27209e1_d27210e1_d27211e1\">Select or create the library to hold the\n                     glyph.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">If the library does not yet contain glyphs, the Insert Glyph dialog is\n                        displayed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fir1665702809557__p_d27212e1_d27213e1_d27214e1\">You can choose to immediately define a new\n                        glyph or click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Cancel</span> to go to the glyph editor.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"fir1665702809557__fig_d27215e1_d27216e1_d27217e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Glyph Editor</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Glyph Editor\" class=\"image\" id=\"fir1665702809557__image_g5x_wfj_d1c\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/defineglyphr.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13895e1_d13896e1_d13897e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To create a glyph:\n </span>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13898e1_d13899e1_d13900e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"fir1665702809557__p_d27221e1_d27222e1_d27223e1\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New</span> in the\n                     glyph editor (Define Glyphs). </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">The Insert Glyph dialog is displayed.</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13901e1_d13902e1_d13903e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"fir1665702809557__p_d27224e1_d27225e1_d27226e1\">Click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span>\n                     button beside the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Primary File</span>, and select the image\n                     created as the primary source. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Uniface automatically detects the size and colors of the image.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"fir1665702809557__fig_d27227e1_d27228e1_d27229e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Insert Glyph</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Insert Glyph dialog\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/insertglyph.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13904e1_d13905e1_d13906e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"fir1665702809557__p_d27233e1_d27234e1_d27235e1\">Optionally, do the same for the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Secondary File</span> to load a secondary version of the image.\n You can create multiple items for each glyph. At run time Uniface displays the variant that is appropriate to the environment, for example, a 16-bit color glyph instead of a 32-bit color glyph.</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13907e1_d13908e1_d13909e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Ensure that the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Display</span> check box is selected for each source file specified, otherwise the glyph will not be displayed at runtime.\n </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13910e1_d13911e1_d13912e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"fir1665702809557__p_d27236e1_d27237e1_d27238e1\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> to load the\n                     images and return to the glyph editor. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">Uniface generates a glyph name by prefixing the primary image name with\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">U_</code>, and puts the original file name in the\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Description</span>. </div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep substepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13913e1_d13914e1_d13915e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Edit the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Glyph Name</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Language</span>.\n </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13916e1_d13917e1_d13918e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"fir1665702809557__p_d27239e1_d27240e1_d27241e1\">To compile and save the glyph, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Save</span></span>. Alternatively, click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span> to compile and store\n               the glyph, and close the editor.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"fir1665702809557__note_w3921ab1b5b3b5b3b1_w3922ab1b5b3b5b3_w3923ab1b5b3b5_w3924ab1b5b3_w3925ab1b5_w3926ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> After the glyph has been defined and stored, it is not possible to\n                  change its properties. If you want to do so, you must delete it and redefine it.\n                  For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vng1705582774408.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vng1705582774408.html\" title=\"You cannot modify a glyph directly in Uniface. You must first export the image to a file and modify it using your preferred image editor, before replacing the glyph in Uniface.\">Modifying Glyphs</a>. </div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"fir1665702809557__li_d13919e1_d13920e1_d13921e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">To delete a glyph, select it and choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Edit</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Delete Glyph</span></span>. </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5827423\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5827423\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Create and Maintain Glyphs Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 23, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Create and Maintain Glyphs Glyphs are maintained and deployed in a runtime library. Using your preferred graphical tools, create one or more images to use as sources for the glyph items. For more information, see Glyphs . Open the glyph editor: Choose More Editors > Glyphs . Select or create the library to hold the glyph. If the library does not yet contain glyphs, the Insert Glyph dialog is displayed. You can choose to immediately define a new glyph or click Cancel to go to the glyph editor. Figure 1. Glyph Editor To create a glyph: Click New in the glyph editor (Define Glyphs). The Insert Glyph dialog is displayed. Click the >> button beside the Primary File , and select the image created as the primary source. Uniface automatically detects the size and colors of the image. Figure 2. Insert Glyph Optionally, do the same for the Secondary File to load a secondary version of the image. You can create multiple items for each glyph. At run time Uniface displays the variant that is appropriate to the environment, for example, a 16-bit color glyph instead of a 32-bit color glyph. Ensure that the Display check box is selected for each source file specified, otherwise the glyph will not be displayed at runtime. Click OK to load the images and return to the glyph editor. Uniface generates a glyph name by prefixing the primary image name with U_ , and puts the original file name in the Description . Edit the Glyph Name and Language . To compile and save the glyph, choose File > Save . Alternatively, click OK to compile and store the glyph, and close the editor. Note: After the glyph has been defined and stored, it is not possible to change its properties. If you want to do so, you must delete it and redefine it. For more information, see Modifying Glyphs . To delete a glyph, select it and choose Edit > Delete Glyph . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}